Usage: stgrinder2 [-options] -i <instem> -o <outstem>
    <instem>            : prefix of .bfloat input file
    <outstem>           : prefix of .bfloat output file
  options:
    -firstslice <int>   : first slice number to process
    -nslices <int>      : number of slices to process
    -a <int>            : active condition
    -c <int>            : control condition
    -delsign s1 s2 s3 ...: sign to apply to each delay point (-1,0,+1)
    -diff               : unpaired t-test (image-by-image)
    -mdiff <int> <int>  : maximum unpaired t-test (within range of delays)
    -corr               : correlate time courses
    -ircorr             : correlate with impulse response
    -delta <float>      : impulse response delta
    -tau <float>        : impulse response tau
    -ndelta <int>       : number of impulse response delays
    -ntau <int>         : number of impulse response delays
    -drange <float> <float> : impulse response delay range
    -trange <float> <float> : impulse response tau range
    -noversample <int>  : number of samples per TR
    -nopval             : don't save p values
    -log10              : use log10 for p values
    -whitenoise         : assume white noise
    -pscale <float>     : multiply pvalues by scale

    MAXT = 30, MAXDOF = 200

